ctrl+l-----to clear
ctrl+z----to push background
fg---to comes into foreground
cd
popd,cd -,pushd <path> -----to go back
top----to see the status of running things

ctrl+r ---open search to find any command

!<number comes in history>------to run the attached command
histtimeformat="%y-%m-%d %t "---enter history---to see the date and time of the history


tail -f <path or filename>--(eg./var/log/syslog)----to go to end of the nay paragraph

truncate -s 0 <filename>----delete the items of the files
 mount | column -t ------- to see the mounted files on system
